ProtoResult:
. "Let $X_1$, $X_2$, \ldots, $X_n$ be continuous random 
   variables with density functions $f_1(x),~f_2(x), 
   \ldots,~f_n(x)$. Then these random variables are { mutually 
   independent\/} if and only if $$f(x_1, x_2, \ldots, x_n) = 
   f_1(x_1)f_2(x_2) \cdots f_n(x_n)$$ for any choice of $x_1, 
   x_2, \ldots, x_n$."
